latestPosts.caption:
Started celebrating my birthday early this weekend at @bahrslandingrestaurant! 

If you followed me from the beginning when I started my foodie page, you have heard me rave about this place. Bahrs is located in Highlands, NJ right by the water! I haven‚Äôt been here since the summer and I‚Äôve missed it! This place is my absolute favorite when the sun is out and people are hanging on the deck at the outdoor bar. But I‚Äôve been missing it so much that I had to go back even though it was cold and rainy out!

The sangria here is my favorite so we had to order a pitcher. They give biscuits instead of bread and they are so buttery and warm. We started with oysters and mussels which were outstanding.

I‚Äôm always ordering the fisherman‚Äôs platter when I come because I love a taste of everything! The scallops are to die for! My mom ordered the Grilled Mexican Shrimp which is actually a special right now!

This place was in a Super Bowl commercial so maybe you recognize it from there! Add this to your summer bucket list and you won‚Äôt be disappointed! 

I‚Äôve already done a reel on this place so head over to the reels tab on my page to find it to see other dishes I‚Äôve ordered here before! 
.
.
.

latestPosts.caption:
Cranford is so lucky to have a spot like The Garrison take over the Kilkenny House location! 

Today I met @fo0odforfun for some after work drinks and I am so mad at myself for not stopping in sooner. You can sit at the bar or at a table and order drinks and pay directly from your phone. It‚Äôs so easy and the service is wonderful. 

I tried ‚ÄúThe Eastside‚Äù and the ‚ÄúHello Cranford‚Äù. The Eastside is made from my favorite gin Hendricks, lime, simple syrup, cucumber, and mint! The ‚ÄúHello Cranford‚Äù was sooo good and  made with Tito‚Äôs, St. Germain, lemon juice, grapefruit, and soda. The name is too cute!

This is such a great place to stop in for a great cocktail or glass of wine. They also have great food options like pizza and small plates because they are owned by the fabulous @wonder !!! 

If you haven‚Äôt been yet, stop in soon! 
.
